The [**`$elemMatch`**](https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/projection/elemMatch/) projection operator provides a way to alter the returned documents, in here coupled with [**`$find`**](https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/method/db.collection.find/#db.collection.find) utilizing second parameter which is **`projection`** will achieve that.

    Post.find(
      {},
      {
        _id: 0,
        photo: { $elemMatch: { _id: id } }
      }
    );

**This will provide leaned documents with the promise: `.lean().exec()`:**

    Post.find(
      {},
      {
        _id: 0,
        photo: { $elemMatch: { _id: id } }
      }
    )
      .lean()
      .exec();

**NOTE:** `$elemMatch` behaviour is to return the first document where `photo`&#39;s `id` matches.

